news_header: Vaccine efficacy varies; influenza cases rise in Finland despite vaccination, with ongoing virus mutations affecting protection.
news_original_title: Influenssaepidemia kiihtyy – tartunnan voi saada rokotteesta huolimatta, muistuttaa asiantuntija
news_text: Experts note that influenza vaccine efficacy ranges from 50-70%, and cases are rising in Finland despite vaccination. The virus mutates rapidly, complicating protection. Current data on vaccine effectiveness will be available in March.
